Here is a brief and simple HTML/JS code to create a colorful website using the notebook sketch with two real jokes:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: lightblue;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    h1 {
      color: purple;
    }
    button {
      background-color: orange;
      color: white;
      font-size: 1.2em;
      margin-top: 10px;
      padding: 10px;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
  <p id="joke1">Why do we never tell secrets on a farm?</p>
  <button onclick="showPunchline('punchline1')">Push to reveal punchline</button>
  <p id="punchline1" hidden>Because the potatoes have eyes and the corn has ears!</p>

  <p id="joke2">Why don't scientists trust atoms?</p>
  <button onclick="showPunchline('punchline2')">Push to reveal punchline</button>
  <p id="punchline2" hidden>Because they make up everything!</p>

  <p>Copyright OpenAI 2023</p>

  <script>
    function showPunchline(punchlineId) {
      document.getElementById(punchlineId).hidden = false;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code creates a simple and colorful webpage with a light blue background and a purple heading. The jokes and buttons are displayed on the page, and when the user clicks the "Push to reveal punchline" button, the respective punchlines will be revealed using JavaScript.

Here's a simple HTML and JavaScript code to create the joke website based on the sketch:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: lightblue;
            text-align: center;
        }
        h1 {
            color: darkblue;
            margin-bottom: 50px;
        }
        p#joke {
            font-size: 24px;
            color: darkgreen;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        button {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: white;
            background-color: darkorange;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border: none;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
    <p id="joke">Funny Joke</p>
    <button onclick="getJoke()">Push to reveal punchline</button>

    <script>
        async function getJoke() {
            const response = await fetch('https://api.chucknorris.io/jokes/random');
            const data = await response.json();
            document.getElementById('joke').innerHTML = data.value;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code snippet creates a simple colorful webpage with a heading "My Joke Website", a joke placeholder, and a button to reveal the punchline. It fetches a joke from the Chuck Norris Jokes API (https://api.chucknorris.io/jokes/random) when the user clicks the button.
